cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR

This paper discusses the theoretical contributions of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) with a focus on image/visual applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also touches upon the neural network architecture of GANs, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and discusses the limitations of GANs, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
